# No eslint-disable — EVER

**NEVER** add `eslint-disable`, `eslint-disable-next-line`, or `eslint-disable-line`
comments in any form. This is a hard rule with zero exceptions.

If ESLint flags an issue, **fix the root cause**:

- `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` → add proper types
- `@next/next/no-img-element` → use `next/image` (`Image`) component
- `unicorn/*` rules → follow the suggested modern JS pattern
- Any other rule → understand why it exists and write compliant code

If a rule is genuinely wrong for the entire project, disable it in
`eslint.config.js` at the config level — never inline.

This policy is enforced by `@eslint-community/eslint-comments/no-use` in the
ESLint config, which will error on any `eslint-disable` comment.
